casualty of frivolous investments, generational dilution, and dwindling det=
ermination. Even the colossal wealth of Cornelius Vanderbilt =E2=80=94 wort=
h $227 billion when adjusted for inflation, giving him a cool $96 billion e=
dge over Bezos =E2=80=94 dissolved in his expanding gene pool.=C2=A0
All of which is to say: that Tata is here at all is remarkable.=C2=A0
