ize: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">A message to all the tyco=
ons out there: beware of your grandchild.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a=
1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">Though the Bibl=
e advances the parable of the prodigal son &#8212; the wasteful offspring t=
hat fritters a father&#8217;s money &#8212; statistically, it is the third =
generation that marks the end of a family fortune. One American study indic=
ated that 90% of wealth evaporates by that point, the casualty of frivolous=
 investments, generational dilution, and dwindling determination. Even the =
colossal wealth of Cornelius Vanderbilt &#8212; worth $227 billion when adj=
usted for inflation, giving him a cool $96 billion edge over Bezos &#8212; =
dissolved in his expanding gene pool.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; =
font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">All of which is to =
say: that Tata is here at all is remarkable.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color: #1=
a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">Four generat=
ions and more than 150 years after its founding, Tata is not only still sta=
nding but essential. Just this week, the company aided in India&#8217;s cor=
onavirus response, agreeing to contribute 800 tonnes of oxygen per day to h=
ealth facilities in need. Far from an isolated example, such civic-mindedne=
ss is at the heart of Tata&#8217;s history, no doubt part of the reason one=
 Twitter commentator <a href=3D"https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkEGOhC=
AQRU_TLE1RgOKCxWzmGgah2iajYACn4-0H28UkBOqnUvU_z9lKS8qn2VOp7Lqmeu5kIr3LSrVSZ=
kehPAVveI9aKDkyb6TnWmkWyvTMRJsNq6n5ILYf8xqcrSHFzwQAKvYynisQTioatFKDVThL1_Mn=
F87xkQZ1-9rDB4qODP1SPlMktppXrXt5iK8HfrdT3-FK1Lm0NRVT9LSvx0ZNlGrrUVrBhR40Kgl=
qQESlRN9yGgTk0EJwVL2AjneAAgeHvQWHElCjFETCjhr6WT2BPyRsC3blmNtm93NZsmxiqnPKIS=
6t_fOyG62fRvv21N7tiKGeE0U7r-RvIvUG-2E0LRQpN-B-svXCCSD7HhAk3AQaMqH0yAehWXP2q=
U3Ff9M_cOeLcQ" style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">referr=
ed</a> to it as India&#8217;s &#8220;parallel government.&#8221; Over a cen=
tury and a half, the conglomerate has supported (and commercialized) Indian=
 life, unlike any other company. In the process, Tata has constructed a diz=
zying tessellate of over 100 businesses, from automobiles to apparel, steel=
 production to tea.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; l=
ine-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">And yet, there&#8217;s the sense that=
 despite its durability, Tata&#8217;s may be in decline. With infighting be=
leaguering the founding families and legacy businesses struggling to adapt =
to a digital world, Tata will need to work hard to ensure it remains a pote=
nt force. To do so, the company will need to shed legacy baggage, embrace t=
he opportunities the tech sector presents, and lean into the essence of wha=
t makes Tata an enduring brand.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-s=
ize: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">In today&#8217;s piece, w=
e&#8217;ll explore:&nbsp;</p><ol style=3D"margin: 1em 0;"><li style=3D"marg=
in: 3.75px 0 3.75px 7.5px; mso-special-format: bullet;"><p style=3D"color: =
#1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0;"><strong>Tata&#8217=
;s rich history, beginning with the opium trade</strong></p></li><li style=
=3D"margin: 3.75px 0 3.75px 7.5px; mso-special-format: bullet;"><p style=3D=
"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0;"><strong>Th=
e complexion of a messy conglomerate</strong></p></li><li style=3D"margin: =
3.75px 0 3.75px 7.5px; mso-special-format: bullet;"><p style=3D"color: #1a1=
a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0;"><strong>The necessary =
moves to perpetuate the dynasty</strong></p></li></ol><h2 style=3D"-moz-osx=
